# Strings
A String is a sequence of characters.
Example:
text = "Hello"

 1. Create and Print String
text = "Hello Python"
print(text)
Output
Hello Python

 2. Access Characters (Indexing)
text = "Python"
print(text[0])
print(text[3])
Output
P
h

 3. String Length
text = "Python"
print(len(text))
Output
6

 4. String Slicing
text = "Python"
print(text[0:3])
print(text[2:5])
Output
Pyt
tho

 5. Convert Case
text = "python"
print(text.upper())
print(text.lower())
Output
PYTHON
python

 6. Check Substring
text = "Hello Python"
print("Python" in text)
Output
True

 7. Replace String
text = "Hello World"
print(text.replace("World", "Python"))
Output
Hello Python

 8. Split String
text = "apple,banana,mango"
print(text.split(","))
Output
['apple', 'banana', 'mango']

 9. Join Strings
words = ["I", "love", "Python"]
print(" ".join(words))
Output
I love Python

 10. Reverse String
text = "Python"
print(text[::-1])
Output
nohtyP

 11. Palindrome Check
text = "madam"
if text == text[::-1]:
    print("Palindrome")
else:
    print("Not Palindrome")
Output
Palindrome

